        private boolean noData(java.lang.String str)
        Checks if there is no data left in the strength. (If string length ==1 and the char which represents the string length 1 is '?'. Then this boolean will be true meaning no data is left, otherwise false meaning keep going.
        Parameters:
        str - the string to be checked for data presence
        Returns:
        true if reaches end of string with data - '?'
